definitions.definition: The language spoken by the Algonquins, a transitional language between Ojibwe and Abenaki .

subdefinitions.definition: A community in Augusta township, United Counties of Leeds and Grenville , Ontario , Canada .

A place in the United States : A village in McHenry County and Kane County , Illinois . A township in McHenry County , Illinois . A neighbourhood of Louisville , Kentucky . A census-designated place in Dorchester County , Maryland . An unincorporated community in Bohemia Township, Ontonagon County , Michigan .
